
JSON PATH TESTING 
===================


Scenario 19:
=================

Use FilterProxy.xml to test Json Path filter functionality. 

curl -v -X POST -d @Filter.json -H "Content-Type: application/json"  http://localhost:8281/services/FilterProxy


Scenario 20 :
===================

Use SwitchProxy.xml to test Json Path filter functionality. 

curl -v -X POST -d @switch1.json -H "Content-Type: application/json"  http://localhost:8281/services/SwitchProxy

curl -v -X POST -d @switch2.json -H "Content-Type: application/json"  http://localhost:8281/services/SwitchProxy


Scenario 21 :
==============

Use PropertyTest.xml to test Json Path filter functionality. 

curl -v -X POST -d @PropertyTest.json -H "Content-Type: application/json"  http://localhost:8281/services/PropertyTest

For array of objects :

curl -v -X POST -d @PropertyArrayTest.json -H "Content-Type: application/json"  http://localhost:8281/services/PropertyArrayTest


Scenario 22 :
=================

Use TestProxy.xml to test payload factory with json path.


curl -v -X POST -d @logTest.json -H "Content-Type: application/json"  http://localhost:8281/services/TestProxy

